               <note type="abstract">Gabriel of Beth Qustan was from Beth Qustan and became bishop of Qartmin.  His body was exhumed to avoid an onslaught of the plague.  He fled marriage to become a monk.  He was the superior of Qartmin and met the Calif Ibn al-Hattab.  He performed miracles and set out the measurements of the monastery of Qartmin.  </note>
